Such renderings as seemed to be neces- sary in English, but which did not accord with the Latin concep- tion, have been given in their connection as examples. In this way it is hoped the pupil or teacher may find a good English expression without losing sight of the Latin conception, which is, after all, the most important of the three classes of meanings.
